## Why This Is Better Than Simple Keyword Matching

| Aspect | Simple keywords (v1) | 3-Layer Pipeline (v2) |
|---|---|---|
| False positives | High — a slide mentioning "professor X proved theorem Y" would be flagged | Low — density scoring catches real educational content containing metadata words |
| False negatives | High — misses slides without exact keyword matches | Low — LLM fallback catches unusual metadata formats |
| Multilingual | No | Yes — keyword lists for both English & German |
| Cost | Zero | ~Zero (LLM only for 5-10% of ambiguous slides) |
| Adaptability | Rigid | LLM layer naturally adapts to new patterns |
| Positional awareness | No | Yes — first/last slide bonus for metadata detection |

